 or painless—if your palms aren't sweaty or your stomach isn't churning, then you probably aren't really practicing digital leadership.The Engaged Leader addresses why leaders need to master a new way of developing relationships, which begins by stepping out of traditional hierarchies; how to listen at scale, share to shape, and engage to transform; the art of making this transformative mind shift; and the science of applying the right tools to meet your strategic goals.This transformation is not optional. Those who choose not to make this change will be abandoned for those who inspire people to follow them.The Engaged Leader provides leaders with the skills and confidence they need to transform their leadership, and in turn, their organizations. The Engaged Leader also provides guidance to institutions—businesses, communities, and schools—on how to develop and nurture digital leadership. It is a must read for anyone who values a deeper connection between leaders and those they serve.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aInternet. 0aLeadership. 0aOnline social networks. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Leadership.2bisacsh  abusiness leaders.  abusinesses.  acommunities.  adigital era.  adigital leadership.  alistening at scale.  anew technologies.  aschools.  astrategic goals.  atechnological innovations.  atransformative mind shift.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Pennsylvania Press Complete Package 2014-2015z978311066593240uhttps://doi.org/10.9783/9781613630532?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781613630532423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781613630532/original  a978-3-11-066593-2  University of Pennsylvania Press Complete Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEB